author: Brian Gormley
title: Breyer Leads $25 Million Bet on Health-Care AI Startup
text:
When Jim Breyer invested in Facebook in 2005, he never expected social networking to be where it is today. Now he’s betting the intersection of artificial intelligence and medicine is poised for its own big breakout.
Mr. Breyer and his firm, Breyer Capital, are leading a $25 million Series A round for Paige.AI, a startup applying AI to pathology to improve diagnosis and treatment of cancer.
